{# "Load more" placeholder row for the Transaction History card (LRA-45).

   Wrapped in a <tr> so its `outerHTML` HTMX swap drops in valid table
   structure (a sequence of <tr> rows plus a fresh placeholder). The
   button's hx-target is the parent <tr>, not the button itself, so the
   replacement happens at the row level.

   Expects:
     - householdId: string
     - memberId:    string
     - nextPage:    int
     - pageSize:    int
#}
<tr class="js-history-loadmore" data-testid="history-loadmore-row">
    <td colspan="6" class="px-3 py-3 text-center">
        <button
            type="button"
            data-testid="history-loadmore"
            hx-get="{{ path('member_history_page', {
                householdId: householdId,
                memberId: memberId,
                page: nextPage,
                pageSize: pageSize,
            }) }}"
            hx-target="closest tr"
            hx-swap="outerHTML"
            class="rounded-md border border-litrec-border bg-litrec-surface px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-semibold text-litrec-text hover:bg-litrec-bg-muted focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-litrec-primary"
        >
            Load more
        </button>
    </td>
</tr>
